        <div class="row2">
            <h2> <!-- 需要回答的问题2 -->
                If memory is built from shared stories, which dreams do you want written into the past? 
            </h4>
            <br> <!-- 问题2答案 -->
            <h4>In the past, I was very afraid to face all my imperfections. But now I'm learning to get along with these "imperfections on the circle", and it is precisely these parts that make up the distinct me. I want to keep countless moments when my resume was rejected. Without these moments, it seems that the last little achievement would become even more insignificant. These not-so-smooth moments instead remind me of how difficult and remarkable it is to achieve each small milestone. I want to keep countless red crosses from my middle school days. These deduction points bear witness to my efforts, and how I went from knowing nothing at the beginning to gradually mastering every knowledge point through hard work. I want to keep the experiences of failed relationships. Through these experiences, I gradually learned how to love myself and others, balance altruism and self-interest, and learn to consider others' feelings while also paying attention to myself. If it weren't for all those stories, I wouldn't have been brave and effective in seizing every new opportunity that comes in the future. So, the idea of keeping these is not to celebrate the "narrative of suffering", but to thank myself along the way and all the people and things that have helped me.
            </h3>
            <br>
            <img src="assets/images/failure.png" alt="failure" min-width="800px">
            <br>
        </div>
